\v 6  \add You dragged away\add* the people of Jerusalem and \add other places in\add* Judah, and you took them far away and sold them to people in Greece.   
\p
\v 7 But I will cause my people to want to return from the places to which you sold them, and I will do to you what you did to them.  
\v 8 Then I will cause \add some of\add* your sons and your daughters to be sold to the people of Judah! And \add some of\add* them will be sold to the Sabea people-group, who live far away. \add That will certainly happen because I\add*, \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*, have said it.”   
\s1 God will judge and punish the nations  
\q1
\v 9 Proclaim to the \add people of all\add* nations,  
\q2 “Prepare for \w a|strong="H3068"\w* war!  
\q1 Summon your soldiers,  
\q2 and tell them to stand in their battle positions.   
\q1
\v 10  \add Take\add* your plows and make swords from them,  
\q2 and \add take\add* your pruning knives and make spears from them.  
\q1 \add Even\add* the weak people must \add also\add* be like [MET] \add strong\add* soldiers.   
\q1
\v 11 All you \add people from the\add* nations that are near \add Judah\add*  
\q2 must come quickly and gather \add in the Valley of Judgment\add*.”  
\b  
\q1 But \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*, \add when that happens\add*, send your army \add of angels to attack them\add*!   
\b  
\q1
\v 12 The \add people in\add* the nations near \add Judah\add* must get ready and come to the Valley of Judgment.  
\q2 There \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* will sit and judge \add and punish\add* them.   
\q1
\v 13  \add They are like\add* [MET] crops that are ready to be harvested;  
\q2 so \add strike them like\add* [MET] \add a farmer\add* swings his sickle to cut the grain.  
\q1 They are like [MET] grapes that are piled high in the pits where they will be pressed;  
\q2 because they are very wicked,  
\q1 \add punish them severely\add* [MET] now,  
\q2 like [MET] \add a farmer\add* tramples on the grapes until the pits are full of juice.   
\b  
\q1
\v 14  \add There will be\add* huge crowds of people in that Valley of Judgment.  
\q2 It will soon be the time that \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \add will punish them\add*.   
\q1
\v 15  \add At that time\add* there will be no light from the sun or moon,  
\q2 and the stars will not shine.   
\q1
\v 16 From Zion \add Hill\add* in Jerusalem \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* will shout,  
\q2 and his voice will be like thunder,  
\q2 and his voice will cause the sky and the earth to shake.  
\q1 But \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* will protect [MET] his people;  
\q2 he will be like [MET] \w a|strong="H3068"\w* strong wall behind which the people of Israel will be protected.   
\s1 God’s blessings for his people  
\q1
\v 17  \add Yahweh says\add*, “At that time, you Israeli people will know that I am \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*, your God.  
\q2 I live on Zion, my sacred hill.  
\q1 Jerusalem will be \w a|strong="H3068"\w* sacred \add city\add*,  
\q2 and \add soldiers from\add* other countries will never conquer it again.   
\b  
\q1
\v 18 At that time, there will be vineyards covering [MTY] the hills,  
\q2 and \add your cattle and goats on\add* those hills will produce plenty of milk.  
\q2 The streams in Judah will never dry up.  
\q1 And \w a|strong="H3068"\w* stream will flow from my temple into the Acacia Valley \add northeast of the Dead Sea\add*.   
\q1
\v 19  \add The armies of\add* Egypt and Edom attacked the people of Judah  
\q2 and killed [MTY] many people who had not done anything that was wrong.  
\q1 So \add now\add* those countries will become deserts,   
\q1
\v 20 but there will always be people living in Jerusalem and \add in other places\add* in Judea.   
\q1
\v 21  \add I\add*, \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*, live on Zion \add Hill in Jerusalem\add*,  
\q2 and I will get revenge on the people \add of Egypt and Edom\add* who killed [MTY] \add many of my people\add*.”   